\description{
Estimate per-development-link incremental loss intensities
\eqn{g_k = \mathbb{E}[\Delta L_k / C^P_k]} from a \code{"Triangle"} and
return an \code{"IntensityFit"} object that bundles the link-level
WLS-estimated intensities along with their standard errors and
diagnostic statistics.

This is the factor-level diagnostic for the exposure-driven (ED)
workflow, parallel to \code{\link[=fit_ata]{fit_ata()}} for the multiplicative (chain
ladder) side. Both operate at the \emph{factor level} without
producing a full projection. For full ED projection (cumulative
loss / premium / lr), use \code{\link[=fit_ed]{fit_ed()}} which accepts either a
\code{Triangle} or an \code{IntensityFit} (skipping a rebuild of the link
table when factors are already computed).
}
\section{ED has no maturity concept}{

Unlike ATA factors, where CV / RSE drive a \code{detect_maturity()}
threshold, ED intensities behave differently — as \eqn{g_k \to 0}
in late development the CV / RSE blow up by construction, not by
instability. \code{fit_intensity()} therefore deliberately omits a
\code{maturity} parameter, and \code{detect_maturity()} rejects
\code{IntensityFit} input with an informative error.
}

